Linux Debugger

A ptrace-based debugger for AArch64 Linux. Supports breakpoints, stepping, register inspection, memory reading, backtracing, DWARF symbol resolution, and disassembly.

## Build

Requires binutils-dev and libdw-dev:

    sudo apt install binutils-dev libdw-dev

    g++ debugger.cpp breakpoint.cpp DWARF_parser.cpp -o debugger -lbfd -lopcodes -ldw

## Usage

    ./debugger <program>

## Commands

    b <addr|func>       set breakpoint at address or function name
    bl                  list breakpoints
    bd <id|addr>        disable breakpoint
    enable <id|addr>    enable breakpoint
    del <id|addr>       delete breakpoint
    c                   continue execution
    s                   single-step one instruction
    n                   step over (next line)
    regs                print all registers
    x/<count> <addr>    read memory (e.g. x/4 0x4006c0)
    bt                  print backtrace
    disasm [addr|func]  disassemble 10 instructions from addr, func, or current PC
    q                   quit and kill tracee
    h                   help
